<subSubSection id="13981D451E752736B1F6EDE9511661B5" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="45DD79582D41C6E52EE0188E6B7FFC32" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CECADA9FA9389F08D539F3E51DFF198B" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Pileus fuscous and densely covered with tiny, deep brown fur or scales, distinctly radially striped with darkened lines. Stipe white, upper part slight brown when old. Cheilocystidia present. Pileipellis without coarse excrescences.</paragraph>
