<subSubSection id="4327EF387E0AD2970050DAF2DC18A54A" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="54A51E71D9B35892BAA66D1A424C1884" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="56817B2E0E7EA445DC4AEA46A628464E" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">The name refers to the centrally depressed, umbilicate basidiocarps, which resemble an eye or a loudspeaker; zhujian is a mythical one-eyed Chinese creature who is usually very noisy, like a walking loudspeaker.</paragraph>
